[It is still not clear whether this is _P. falciparum_ or _P. vivax_.
We presume it is _P. falciparum_.

The website of the Queensland Public Health Authority
(http://www.health.qld.gov.au/) contains no information on the
outbreak. The statement that "malaria is not an infectious disease" is
probably a misquote. Infectious diseases include infections
transmitted between humans by insects.

For the ProMED-mail HealthMap of the Torres Strait Islands, see
http://healthmap.org/r/0Fcg. - Mod.EP]
